// TerminalTab
// Full-screen terminal container for mobile with multi-tab support.
// Wraps XTermTerminal instances in a MobileTerminalTabBar layout.
// All terminals are always mounted; only the active one is visible (display:flex
// vs display:none) to preserve their state across tab switches.
// Triggers a resize event via double-RAF when the active tab changes.

FUNCTION TerminalTab(tabs, activeTabId, activeTab, isLoading, error, onTabSelect, onTabClose, onTabAdd) -> JSX  EXPORT
  CALLS: XTermTerminal (XTermTerminal), MobileTerminalTabBar (MobileTerminalTabBar)
  IF isLoading: shows "Loading terminals..." placeholder.
  IF error: shows error message + "Try Again" button (calls onTabAdd).
  IF tabs is empty: shows "No active terminal" + "New Terminal" button.
  ELSE: renders MobileTerminalTabBar + a terminal content area.
  Terminal content area renders all tabs as XTermTerminal instances; only the
  active tab has display:flex, others have display:none.
  On activeTabId change, dispatches a resize event on the wrapper element via
  double-RAF to ensure the terminal fits after the visibility change.
